&gt; cessation of mental activity and entering samadhi OR\n&gt; aw=\r\nakening of Kundalini and progress towards samadhi.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; If one reach=\r\nes samadhi directly when Kundalini awakens,\n&gt; things are fine. But, that ma=\r\ny not happen. Kundalini can\n&gt; take many different paths and go to different=\r\n places.\n&gt; Depending on the impurities in various nadis, various\n&gt; experien=\r\nces are possible. If a sadhaka is unprepared to\n&gt; handle the experience, it=\r\n can create problems. One can\n&gt; experience something nice and become proud =\r\nand egoistic and\n&gt; get stuck there. One can experience a very fierce form o=\r\nf\n&gt; divine and get scared to death or go mad. Many possibilities\n&gt; are ther=\r\ne.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; Thus, practices that can truly awaken one were kept limited\n=\r\n&gt; to the initiated. Guru would assess the progress and\n&gt; readiness of a sad=\r\nhaka and initiate one when one is ready.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; However, there are a few things that are different in\n&gt; today&#39;s t=\r\nimes:\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; (1) There are very few people who are ready to experience=\r\n\n&gt; something. Most people will just do sadhana, burn some basic\n&gt; blocking =\r\nkarmas and not really experience much. At most,\n&gt; some people will experien=\r\nce an awakening and just a little\n&gt; movement of Kundalini.\n&gt; \n&gt; (2) There a=\r\nre very few gurus who are indeed capable of\n&gt; assessing and guiding a sadha=\r\nka well. Most initiations are a\n&gt; mere formality.\n&gt; \n&gt; (3) With the insiste=\r\nnce on initiation etc, we may be\n&gt; blocking, in the coming years, the very =\r\nfew sadhakas who MAY\n&gt; actually achieve some progress with a mantra, from e=\r\nven\n&gt; trying it.\n&gt; \n&gt; (4) If a sadhaka surrenders and has the attitude of &quot;=\r\nI\n&gt; do not know the right way. I am just doing what I am capable\n&gt; of. Plea=\r\nse take care of me Mother&quot;, none of the risks I\n&gt; mentioned above will real=\r\nly apply.\n&gt; \n&gt; (5) Especially if one does not engage in raja yoga/hatha\n&gt; y=\r\noga practices that are meant to forcefully awaken and raise\n&gt; Kundalini and=\r\n if one does not consciously think in terms of\n&gt; raising Kundalini, one is =\r\nsafe.\n&gt; \n&gt; (6) If one is not looking for any specific results and\n&gt; doing a=\r\n mantra just for spiritual progress with a sense of\n&gt; surrender, one is saf=\r\ne.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; Apart from assessing the rea=\r\ndiness, there are some more\n&gt; functions performed by an initiating guru:\n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; (1) A guru can jumpstart one&#39;s sadhana with a mantra\n&gt; and result=\r\ns can come faster.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; However, this expects a guru of some caliber=\r\n and\n&gt; achievement with the mantra. After all, if one wants a\n&gt; one-on-one =\r\naudience with Sachin Tendulkar or Roger Federer\n&gt; or Barack Obama, being in=\r\ntroduced to them by someone they\n&gt; know and someone that had a one-on-one a=\r\nudience with them\n&gt; earlier can be helpful (instead of introducing by onese=\r\nlf).\n&gt; If someone who merely read more about them but is not any\n&gt; closer t=\r\no them tries to introduce you to them, will it even\n&gt; get their attention?\n=\r\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; Now-a-days, most people do not have access to gurus who\n&gt; have =\r\nexperienced the divine with a mantra. Such people are\n&gt; very rare. One&#39;s be=\r\nst bet is to do sadhana by oneself,\n&gt; using all the tools given by rishis a=\r\nnd various spiritual\n&gt; masters. When one is ready (and if it is needed), a =\r\nguru may\n&gt; come and take one&#39;s sadhana to the next level.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; (2) A=\r\n guru can mould the correct attitude in sadhaka before\n&gt; a sadhana is taken=\r\n up.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; However, there are sadhakas initiated in powerful mantras\n=\r\n&gt; and not having the right attitude. For example, I know\n&gt; people initiated=\r\n into Bagalamukhi mantra and trying to use\n&gt; it to win litigation. If one d=\r\noes not know that a\n&gt; &quot;Mahavidya&quot; (supreme knowledge) is for overcoming\n&gt; c=\r\nonditioning and realizing self and not for winning court\n&gt; cases, one&#39;s ini=\r\ntiation is no good.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; On the other hand, I know some people not f=\r\normally\n&gt; initiated into Chandipath, but doing Chandi homam daily with\n&gt; sa=\r\nptashati and also navarna mantra. I know that they do not\n&gt; have any specif=\r\nic material goals and are overcoming the few\n&gt; desires that were originally=\r\n there at the back of the mind.\n&gt; The are making quick progress spiritually=\r\n and their thinking\n&gt; is getting transformed nicely. Despite having no form=\r\nal\n&gt; initiation, aren&#39;t they worshipping Chandi as a\n&gt; Mahavidya?\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt; Bottomline is that one can mould one&#39;s own attitude\n&gt; through a formal i=\r\nnitiation or through reading scriptures,\n&gt; satsanga and constant contemplat=\r\nion. One thing may work\n&gt; better in one case and another thing in another c=\r\nase.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; (3) A guru can teach the correct procedure of a sadhana.\n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; However, role of procedural correctness in success is a\n&gt; higher=\r\n in sadhanas for specific results than sadhana for\n&gt; spiritual progress. I =\r\nmaintain that the art of getting\n&gt; specific results from sadhanas is being =\r\nhidden more and more\n&gt; as Kali progresses, for a reason. I suggest that it =\r\nis\n&gt; useless to even think in those terms and pursue it.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; Mantra=\r\ns like navarna mantra can just be meditated on,\n&gt; without any specific proc=\r\nedure. When one is ready and pure\n&gt; enough, they can give one an experience=\r\n of the divine.\n&gt; Mantras like Siddha Kunjika stotra, that codify several\n&gt;=\r\n specific sadhanas to get specific results, are anyway\n&gt; inaccessible to mo=\r\nst people of this age! They are only\n&gt; available in codified form and gurus=\r\n who can decode them\n&gt; will keep disappearing more and more.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; * =\r\n       *        *\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; For those who are already doing Sri Sri Cha=\r\nndi path\n&gt; without initiation, there is\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; no need to worry or be confu=\r\nsed. ... Please keep doing\n&gt; whatever you are doing.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; Given this=\r\n statement, the difference of opinion between us\n&gt; are very subtle.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n=\r\n&gt; \n&gt; One word on guilt here. If someone is doing a practice and\n&gt; feels a s=\r\nense of guilt, it blocks the practice from working\n&gt; effectively. Please do=\r\n whatever sadhana you do, without a\n&gt; sense of guilt. If you have the sense=\r\n of guilt, work on\n&gt; overcoming it. If you cannot overcome it, it may be a =\r\ngood\n&gt; idea to find a sadhana with which you feel comfortable and\n&gt; have no=\r\n sense of guilt.\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Things will happen on their own accord in th=\r\ne natural\n&gt; flow. Leave the rest to\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; the compassionate Goddess.\n&gt; \n&gt; =\r\n \n&gt; \n&gt; That&#39;s the bottomline. Even if one were initiated, it\n&gt; would be qui=\r\nte difficult to not leave things to the Goddess\n&gt; and make things happen as=\r\n one wanted. Start sadhana with\n&gt; some level of surrender. Then, sadhana wi=\r\nll help increase\n&gt; the level of surrender. \n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        *=\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; Nagraj garu,\n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; The opinion referred to in your quest=\r\nion 2 is not without\n&gt; basis. But again, we need to understand the motivati=\