i=\r\nth most mantras. Mantras containing bijaksharas,\n&gt; agamic mantras, mantras =\r\nof Mahavidyas etc need initiation.\n&gt; This is the traditional view. Mantras =\r\nfrom the Veda Samhita\n&gt; are not the same as these other mantras that need\n&gt;=\r\n initiation, which are generally referred to as\n&gt; Agamic/Tantrik mantras. W=\r\nhatever you call these mantras the\n&gt; actual idea is that these mantras are =\r\nintegral parts of\n&gt; larger and distinct spiritual specialities that need\n&gt; =\r\ninitiation, as in the case of Mahavidyas such as Kali or\n&gt; Sri.\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt; &gt; 5.\tVishnusahasranama, Sivasahasranama, Aditya hrdayam\n&gt; etc do not nee=\r\nd initiation as they fall under stotra\n&gt; category only. Lalitasahasranama a=\r\nnd Devi Mahatmyam are\n&gt; traditionally viewed not MERELY as stotras or parts=\r\n of\n&gt; puranas. They have a larger status as integral parts of a\n&gt; Mahavidya=\r\n sadhana. Chanting them without initiation is not\n&gt; recommended especially =\r\nwhen the reader combines the navarna\n&gt; or shodashi mantras too as an integr=\r\nal part of the\n&gt; chanting.\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt;            \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; 6.\tI know from persona=\r\nl interaction that acharyas\n&gt; belonging to both Kanchi as well as Sringeri =\r\nparamparas\n&gt; recommend initiation for both the sadhanas of Sri Sri Chandi\n&gt;=\r\n and Sri Vidya along with their respective NAVAKSHARI AND\n&gt; SHODASAKSHARI m=\r\nantras which are treated as an INTEGRAL LIMB\n&gt; (ANGA) of the sadhana. Achar=\r\nyas of both these traditions\n&gt; hold that one needs to be initiated to chant=\r\n the Navarna as\n&gt; well as shodashakshari mantras.\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; 7.\tRecapp=\r\ning my earlier stance, Devi Mahatmyam is a\n&gt; great text that has an indepen=\r\ndent status by itself as part\n&gt; of a Mahavidya. It is simultaneously a Maha=\r\nvidya, a\n&gt; Yogasastra as well as an Advaitic text in the spirit of the\n&gt; Up=\r\nanishads. ***As a Mahavidya the Navakshari is an integral\n&gt; part of Sri Sri=\r\n Chandi path***. Thus tradition holds that\n&gt; one needs to be initiated to c=\r\nhant it. However if one wishes\n&gt; to benefit from the Yoga-Vedanta or Sacred=\r\n myth aspects of\n&gt; the Devi Mahatmyam, , reading the sacred myth in the\n&gt; v=\r\nernacular has been recommended in my write-up, as chanting\n&gt; the original a=\r\nlong with the navakshari  amounts to\n&gt; practicing the sadhana of a Mahavidy=\r\na. In that case it is\n&gt; recommended to be initiated and go through the spec=\r\nialised\n&gt; sadhanas properly under guidance.\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; 8.\tArguably if =\r\nan uninitiated person reads the Devi\n&gt; Mahatmyam in the original Sanskrit a=\r\ns part of the *Pauranik*\n&gt; approach and not as a Mahavidya, it has an inher=\r\nent problem\n&gt; in our times.  The problem with attempting to do a parayana\n&gt;=\r\n of Devi Mahatmyam from texts alone (without initiation) is\n&gt; that most rea=\r\nders inadvertently end up also chanting the\n&gt; Navarna mantra or stotras suc=\r\nh as the Siddhakunjika stotram\n&gt; which too contain the bijaksharas.\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; =\r\n \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; 9.\tI you carefully peruse my write-up on the Devi\n&gt; Mahatmyam, for=\r\nget translating, nowhere do I put down the\n&gt; Navarna mantra even in writing=\r\n. Neither have I attempted to\n&gt; write a commentary on it. Translations of m=\r\nantras do not\n&gt; have the power of the original mantra as Sabda or Vak.\n&gt; Ho=\r\nwever it is recommended to know the essence or import\n&gt; (artha) of the mant=\r\nra and its sadhana while chanting it.\n&gt; Infact `artha&#39; is the import, the e=\r\nssence of `Vak&#39;,\n&gt; not a translation! \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; 10.\tFor those who are=\r\n already doing Sri Sri Chandi\n&gt; path without initiation, there is no need t=\r\no worry or be\n&gt; confused. There has to be a certain level of samskara to be=\r\n\n&gt; attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. We all have it.\n&gt; Otherwise we =\r\nwould not be doing it (initiation or no\n&gt; initiation). Please keep doing wh=\r\natever you are doing. Just\n&gt; be cautious not to do sakama sadhana. As Naras=\r\nimha garu has\n&gt; rightly pointed out it is better to just do the sadhana\n&gt; W=\r\nITHOUT asking for any favours or results. That attitude\n&gt; itself will reduc=\r\ne a lot of the potential problem. Things\n&gt; will happen on their own accord =\r\nin the natural flow. Leave\n&gt; the rest to the compassionate Goddess.        =\r\n      \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Hope the above pointers help in clearing any\n&gt; confus=\r\nion.  \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Regards,\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Satya Prakash                \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; =\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; --- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com,\n&gt; h ram=\r\nalingam &lt;hramalingam@...&gt; wrote:\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt;\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; Namaste everybody\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt;=\r\n &gt; I want to share one anecdote happened in front of\n&gt; Kanchi Maha Sannidan=\r\nam Sri\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; Sri Chandrasekara Bharathi Swamigal\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; When Swamigal =\r\nwas staying in a camp near Mysore\n&gt; in Karnataka One day all the\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; l=\r\nearned persons male and female alike\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; requested Swamigal to transla=\r\nte Sri Vishnu\n&gt; SahasraNamam in kannada language\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; so that they can =\r\nchant knowing the meaning\n&gt; fully.\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; Swamigal didn&#39;t reply to this r=\r\nequest which\n&gt; was made early in the morning.\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; Later in the day aft=\r\ner the days pooja etc were\n&gt; over as usual Postman came to\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; camp to=\r\n deliver the posts cam